00:00:52.133 --> 00:00:54.033
[ Anthony Narrating ]
Every day, when I wake up...

00:00:54.100 --> 00:00:55.933
I still can’t believe I’m at Harvard.

00:00:58.467 --> 00:01:01.400
Like every freshman,
I get to live in Harvard Yard...

00:01:03.633 --> 00:01:05.867
and I get to eat breakfast
in Annenberg Hall.

00:01:05.933 --> 00:01:07.767
- What’s up, you guys?
- Hey.

00:01:08.667 --> 00:01:12.500
I really enjoy my freshman seminar,
“The Evolution of Aging.”

00:01:12.567 --> 00:01:16.267
It’s just me, 15 other students
and a faculty member.

00:01:17.300 --> 00:01:20.700
And I get to work directly with my professor
on research projects.

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:24.333
I’m able to visit any of the other
great Harvard schools...

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:26.333
like the School of Engineering...

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:29.600
or the Kennedy School,
where I’ve heard world leaders speak...

00:01:30.633 --> 00:01:33.100
or the medical school,
which is pretty cool...

00:01:33.167 --> 00:01:36.833
because I’m also training to become an E.M.T.–
I want to become a doctor.

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:41.533
Every day, I get to hang out with my friends
and try something new.

00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:43.400
[ All Shout ]

00:01:43.467 --> 00:01:46.267
Harvard is one university
with a million things to explore...

00:01:47.567 --> 00:01:50.300
and I’m glad I’ve got the next three years
to try them all.

00:01:51.367 --> 00:01:54.067
My name is Anthony,
and I’m from Tucker, Georgia.

00:02:03.333 --> 00:02:08.500
The house system is here to make
whatever you want to do at Harvard possible.

00:02:08.567 --> 00:02:11.367
There are 12 residential Harvard houses.

00:02:11.433 --> 00:02:14.000
[ Female Student ] Each house has
its own dining hall, its own community...

00:02:14.067 --> 00:02:16.033
its own population of students.

00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:20.067
After freshman year, you are randomly
sorted into one of those houses.

00:02:20.133 --> 00:02:23.633
Not only is the house a center
for non-classroom learning...

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:25.767
but it’s also a hub for social activity.

00:02:25.833 --> 00:02:27.633
[ Female Student #2 ]
You all live together and eat together...

00:02:27.700 --> 00:02:29.333
and participate in events together.

00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:31.233
[ Female Student #3 ]
There are people from every country...

00:02:31.300 --> 00:02:33.600
every religion,
and that’s where you really learn.

00:02:33.667 --> 00:02:35.533
A lot of the opportunities that you have...

00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:38.100
to have those
close one-on-one conversations...

00:02:38.167 --> 00:02:42.433
with a professor, with someone
who’s visiting from another university–

00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:45.733
The place where you really get to engage
with those people is in your house.

00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:48.533
[ Man ] Our job’s really
to try and help this house...

00:02:48.600 --> 00:02:52.000
be as vibrant and intellectual
and fun as possible.

00:02:52.067 --> 00:02:54.700
[ Lowell Housemaster ] Lowell House
is a place that has a lot of traditions...

00:02:54.767 --> 00:02:57.533
like having tea on Thursdays at 5:00.

00:02:57.600 --> 00:03:00.333
- [ Female Student #4 ]
There’s an opera every year.
- [ Male Student ] Dances in the house.

00:03:00.400 --> 00:03:02.933
It’s a good time to get to know
other people in the house...

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:05.733
to see your friends,
catch up on the week.

00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:09.367
It’s a place where you can be who you are
and discover who you want to become.

00:03:09.433 --> 00:03:12.733
I think coming back home
is a very comfortable space.

00:03:12.800 --> 00:03:17.100
[ Lowell Housemaster ] This is really an attempt
to create a community within a college.

00:03:17.167 --> 00:03:21.333
This is what makes a Harvard education
very distinctive.

